# Web3 Development Rules

## Security First
- Never hardcode private keys, bot tokens, or API secrets in source code
- Never simulate payments — always use real contract calls (writeContract + sendTransaction)
- Validate all on-chain data server-side, never trust client-side wallet state alone
- Always handle transaction reverts gracefully with user-facing error messages

## Wallet & Payment Flows
- Every payment flow must have these states: connecting, connected, approving, paying, confirming, success, error
- Always show gas estimates before user signs
- Handle wallet disconnection mid-flow (don't assume wallet stays connected)
- Use deeplinks to close web→Telegram loops when applicable

## Smart Contracts
- Check chain ID before every transaction
- Handle different RPC endpoints per environment (testnet vs mainnet)
- Never assume transaction confirmation — wait for receipt

## When in doubt
If any Web3 decision has trade-offs (gas optimization, contract pattern, chain selection), suggest generating a Codex brief via the multi-LLM workflow.
